<P></P>The way I explain it now is that stories don't have to represent =
business=20
value to the customer team, but they do have to represent progress. Only =
the=20
customer team knows what it will consider progress, so they have to do =
the=20
slicing. -- <A href=3D"http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?KentBeck">KentBeck</A> on =
<A=20
href=3D"http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?XpMailingList">XpMailingList</A>=20
<P></P>Can you give an example of a story that does not represent =
business value=20
to the customer? Why would customers consider something progress if it =
does not=20
deliver value to them? -- Chandrashekhar=20
